Date: Fri, 9 Jan 2015 23:51:04 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 047/452] spi-nor: fsl-quadspi: Add fsl_quadspi support for
 LS2085A

Except i.MX platforms, other platforms have Quad SPI controller.
So this patch will remove the dependence on ARCH_MXC.

Signed-off-by: Alison Wang <alison.wang@freescale.com>
Change-Id: I6e16b9ae28446a0b1d6d627881f5115ace297985
Reviewed-on: http://git.am.freescale.net:8181/34981
Tested-by: Review Code-CDREVIEW <CDREVIEW@freescale.com>
Reviewed-by: Stuart Yoder <stuart.yoder@freescale.com>
[Xulin: Original patch taken from FSL LS2085 SDK EAR6.0,
LS2085A-SDK-SOURCE-20160304-yocto.iso]
Signed-off-by: Xulin Sun <xulin.sun@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/mtd/spi-nor/Kconfig |    1 -
 1 files changed, 0 insertions(+), 1 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/mtd/spi-nor/Kconfig b/drivers/mtd/spi-nor/Kconfig
index 64a4f0e..72c9a80 100644
--- a/drivers/mtd/spi-nor/Kconfig
+++ b/drivers/mtd/spi-nor/Kconfig
@@ -23,7 +23,6 @@ config MTD_SPI_NOR_USE_4K_SECTORS
 
 config SPI_FSL_QUADSPI
 	tristate "Freescale Quad SPI controller"
-	depends on ARCH_MXC
 	help
 	  This enables support for the Quad SPI controller in master mode.
 	  We only connect the NOR to this controller now.
